  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Management Associate (Finance and Investment)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage financial and investment portfolios for corporate (B2B) and individual (B2C) clients on Investment, Risk, and Asset Management.</li><li>Analyze financial markets and investment funds across asset classes including Equities, ETFs, Bonds, and Unit Trusts.</li><li>Provide integrated financial solutions focused on Wealth Preservation, Partnership Management, Estate Planning, and Business Succession Planning.</li><li>Onboarding of clients' investment portfolios through iFast Central.</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team setting</li><li>Academic qualification equivalent to <u>one</u> of the following: <br />GCE 'A' Level certificate; International Baccalaureate Diploma; or Diploma awarded by a Polytechnic in Singapore</li></ul><p><strong>Job Type</strong></p><ul><li>Entry level role. Full-time and part-time positions available.</li><li>Open to Career switchers, Undergraduates, and Fresh graduates with no prior finance or investment experience</li><li>Flexible working hours, work from home option available.</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Career advancement opportunities to senior executive and managerial roles</li><li>Comprehensive structured training program with one-on-one mentorship</li><li>Supportive and collaborative team culture promoting work-life balance</li><li>Performance-based incentives, bonuses, and incentivized overseas trips</li></ul>",
